The paper discusses a forward error correction (FEC) scheme for optical communications, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The proposed scheme involves a decoder architecture, which could also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and embedded systems (cs.ET).
